title: Senate Democrats block 'sanctuary cities' legislation
text:
Photo: Drew Anthony Smith, Getty Images Travis County, Texas

WASHINGTON (AP) — Senate Democrats on Tuesday blocked legislation to crack down on "sanctuary cities" that shield residents from federal immigration authorities, casting the bill as anti-immigration policy that echoes the rhetoric of Republican presidential candidate Donald Trump.
